text: Hi. This is Shekhar Srinivasan. In this video we shall understand the differences between the process model of traditional web application development, model View controller, popularly called as MVC Web application development, and our Django Model view template, popularly called as MVT development model. If you haven't subscribed my channel yet, please do subscribe and click on the bell icon to get notified whenever I upload a new video on the latest technologies. This encourages me to create more and more videos. First, let us start with understanding the process model of traditional web application development. Whenever a client sends a request to the server, the request will be given as HTP request to the web server where the server accepts the request, identify the requested web application and then the requested page will be processed within the web server. And if there is any requirement to interact with the database, then the process interacts with the database and then it will generate the result which will be provided as a Http response to the client. Now let us understand how the MVC pattern works. MVC stands for Model View Controller, where Model is responsible for managing the data of the application and it is the application's dynamic data structure which is independent of the user interface and um directly manages the data logic and also the rules of the application. View is responsible for providing the user interface to present the model data in a particular format. Controller is responsible for the complete orchestration. It is used to accept the request and to provide the response to the client. In short, we can consider that model as business layer, view as presentation layer and controller as input control. Now let us understand how the web application developed using MVC will be processed. Whenever a Ah client sends a request to the MVC web application, then the request will be accepted by the controller and the controller can provide the result as a Http response to the client. If the client sends a request for updating the data present within the database, then the controller accepts the request and manipulates the model which will update the database. And then the updated Model details will be received by the controller and then passes the Model Data to the view, where the view uses the Model Data and renders the UI as per the requirement and provides the result to the controller, where the result will be written to the client as ah, a Http response by the controller. One important point we need to remember here is MVC design pattern has been implemented by different companies and vendors. We have ASP net, MVC Spring, MVC ruby on Rails, etc. So some MVC design pattern implementation may vary significantly from the traditional MVC pattern. What I have explained in general. Now let us understand Model View template pattern which is used by the Django Web framework. Uh for its web development. In MVT. Model is used to manage and query data through python Objects models defines the structure of stored data, including the field properties, default values, selection list options, label text for forms, etc. In most of the frameworks, views means web pages or presentation or UI layers where in Django Web framework views Ah are the heart of the Web application, they are used to receive Http requests from the clients and used to return Http response back to the client. In between, they marshall the uh, other resources of the framework to access database, render templates, et cetera. Finally, we have templates which is used to specify the structure of an output document using the placeholders for data that will be filled in when a page is generated. Remember that templates are often used to create HTML content, but it can also be used to create other types of documents. And Django templates can be created using native Templating system, popularly called as Django Template Language, and another popular Python library called as Ginger for creating the template. Now, let us understand how Django Web Application framework works whenever a request has been submitted. Whenever a client sends a request to a Django Web application, then the Django framework accepts the request and submits the request to the URLs, where the URLs acts like a URL mapper to redirect Http requests to the relevant view based on the requested URL. The URL mapper can also match particular pattern of strings or digits that appear in a URL and pass this to a view where the views accepts the request and process the instructions written within the relevant view method and provides the result as a Http response to the client. Now, whenever the client sends a request for a Django Web application for interacting with some database and to fetch some data for visualization, then once again the request will be given to the Django framework, then it will be redirected to the URLs based on the requested URL pattern. The request will be given to the relevant view, where the view will identify the model to be used for interacting with the database and it will read or write the data to the model as per the requirement. And it uses a template to provide an efficient user interface for the client. And once the page has been generated by the template by filling its placeholders with the data from the model view, will provide the result as a Http response to the clients. Hope you have got a fair idea on understanding the difference between traditional web development MVC pattern and MVT pattern used by the Django Web Application framework. If you like this video, don't forget to subscribe my channel m and give a like to this video and click on the bell icon to get the notification of my new videos. See you soon in the next video your shaker close.
